						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I hope there is some magical pin that lets the PPU read from the CPU's address space.  That would allow tons of amazing hardware tricks being done.</div>
<br />
<br />This would be completely impossible. The only data connection between the CPU and the PPU are an 8 bit address (PA7-0) and data bus (CD7-0), allowing the CPU access up to 256 PPU registers. 
<br />
<br />I seriously doubt that a unified memory architecture would have been a wise idea, since the PPU accesses video ram at 5.37 Mhz , which would have left no free memory cycles for the CPU during active display.</div>

